# Agent workflow

Follow these phases so Plan and Ask turns stay read-only and validation runs
only after implementation.

## Phases

1. **Research / Plan** -- Read code, answer questions, create or refine plans.
   No file edits, no `make` targets, no validation subagents.
2. **User review** -- Stop after `CreatePlan` or a proposed approach. Wait for
   explicit approval ("implement", "go ahead", mode switch) before editing.
3. **Implementation** -- Edit files; follow TDD for production logic per
   [testing.mdc](testing.mdc) and [project-guidance.mdc](project-guidance.mdc).
4. **Validation** -- Run scoped checks from [ci-validation.mdc](ci-validation.mdc)
   only after code changes in this session.

## Plan and Ask mode

- Read-only: no Write/StrReplace, no commits, no local CI scans.
- After delivering a plan, **stop**. Do not run `make` targets or launch
  validation subagents until the user approves implementation.
- Do not treat plan delivery, research answers, or code reviews as "declaring
  work done".

## Validation triggers

Run checks only when:

- The user asked to implement and files were edited this session, or
- The user explicitly asks before commit/push or if changes are merge-ready, or
- CI failed on an existing PR (use **ci-investigator**).

Do **not** run validation after read-only turns or when no files were edited.

## Stop hook behavior

The project stop hook follow-up runs only when the agent edited files this
turn (or when a scoped check failed on the prior turn) and required targets
from [pre-merge-check/targets.md](.cursor/skills/pre-merge-check/targets.md)
have not all succeeded yet. Pending paths clear after successful checks. It
does not auto-submit `make check-pr` or `make check-fast`.
